- using all can slow the browser rendering because all properties are checked
- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_animated_properties
- if a property has an identifiable half way point, it can be transitioned.
- http://leaverou.github.io/animatable/
- https://docs.webplatform.org/wiki/css/properties/transform
- transform: rotate(25deg), skewX(10deg), scale(1.1), translateX()
- transform-origin: 50% 50% // default
- http://cubic-bezier.com
- perspective: 700px // creates the illusion of depth for children elements (larger valuse create a shallow perspective, more subtle)
- perspective-origin: 50% 50% // default
- transform: rotateY(55deg), rotateX(55deg) // add to child for 3d result
- transform-style: preserve-3d // child elements of the child will also have 3d
- backface-visibility: hidden // makes the backface hidden
- rotateZ works the same as rotate
- rotate3d(x, y, z, ,) / 1,0,1, 180deg or turn
